         <head id="a1">DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY</head>
         <unittitle label="Title:" encodinganalog="MARC 245">Cornell University Office of Controller records, 
		  <unitdate type="inclusive" encodinganalog="MARC 245">1911-1982.</unitdate>
		
         </unittitle>
         <unitid label="Collection Number:">7-1-1883</unitid>
         <origination label="Creator:"> 
		  
            <corpname encodinganalog="MARC 110">Cornell University. Office of Controller.</corpname>
		
         </origination>
         <physdesc label="Quantity:" encodinganalog="MARC 300">6.4 cubic ft.</physdesc>
         <physdesc label="Forms of Material:">Bonds, contracts, correspondence, blueprints, vouchers, meeting minutes.</physdesc>
         <repository label="Repository:">Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library</repository>
         <abstract label="Abstract:">Budget figures, reports, payroll vouchers, and other records of the Controller of Cornell University.</abstract>
         <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language>
         </langmaterial>
      </did>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Includes bid bonds from various building companies for heating, ventilation, and electrical wiring, bonds to accompany proposals for building work, contract bonds, contracts for University buildings, specifications for labor and materials required for construction, articles of agreement between the University and construction companies or private individuals for construction work or materials, certification of dollars paid out or rebated by architectural firms or construction companies. Also contains a blueprint of Olin Hall, correspondence (with several letters pertaining to the building of Willard Straight Hall and signed by Dorothy Whitney Straight and the Comptroller of the University Charles D. Bostwick, 1924), meeting notes for the Cornell Plantations Committee Meeting (1947-1970), pictures (several of Clara Dickson Hall), and state leases held by the Treasurer's Office.
		  Also budget figures, reports, payroll vouchers, and other records of the Controller of Cornell University.</p>
      </scopecontent>
